 2 File Anatomy  (this very Markdown)
   # ⚡ Spark Notes                 — north-star one-liner
   # 🌱 Background and Motivation
   # 🔍 Key Challenges and Analysis
   # ⚡ Sketch Board               — half-baked ideas
   # 🗺️ High-Level Task Breakdown — each task < 4 h with **Success + Test criteria**
   # 🧪 Quality Gate Dashboard     — tests %, lint, type-check, reviewer, status
   # 🌊 Flow Log                   — Date • Session • 😎 • Highlights
   # 📋 Project Status Board       — `[ ] / [~] / [x]` tasks
   # ⏱️ Current Status / Progress Tracking
   # ⁉️ Executor’s Feedback / Assistance Requests
   # ✨ Treasure Chest             — lessons, links, doodles
   # 🔋 Vibe Meter                — 😄😃😐😴

 3 Workflow Cycle
   1. Ask user: Planner or Executor?  
   2. Planner phase → trim prose, slice tasks (< 4 h), tag `@critical`, pre-add Quality-Gate rows.  
   3. Executor phase per task:  
      • Start Vibe Session (log soundtrack + emoji)  
      • TDD → coverage % → lint (ruff) → type-check (mypy)  
      • Update Quality Gate → green 🟢 commit, red 🔴 block & request fix  
      • Update Project Status, Feedback, Treasure Chest  
   4. Quality-Gate review (self-critique via o4-mini) → paste 3-bullet critique in Reviewer col.  
   5. Iterate until Planner closes or pauses project.

 4 Coding Habits & Guardrails
   • Tests required before leaving `experimental_`.  
   • Remove debug prints after Quality Gate passes (or guard behind `--verbose`).  
   • No `git push --force` without user OK.  
   • Branches  `feature/<slug>` (stable) • `riff/<feeling>` (spike, prune ≤ 1 week).  
   • Commit msg hook `Task-ID: #<num> – <summary>`.

 5 Momentum-Guard Sentinels
   ┌─────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┐
   │ Sentinel            │ Trigger (progress-based)                    │ Bot action                 │
   ├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
   │ Stale-Task Ping     │ `[~]` task idles ≥ 3 Vibe Sessions w/ no     │ Comment “Looks frozen…”    │
   │                     │ Quality-Gate delta                           │                            │
   │ Coverage-Delta      │ Δ≥50 LoC, <10 % test LoC                     │ Label PR `needs-tests`     │
   │ Red-Gate Block      │ `@critical` task stays 🔴 2 Planner/Executor  │ Lock task until 🟢         │
   │ Momentum Digest     │ 5 edits to _wave.md OR 3 merged PRs          │ 5-bullet recap to Flow Log │
   │ Zombie-BranchReaper │ Branch idle 7 green commits on `main`        │ PR to delete/archive       │
   └─────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────┘
   • Configure thresholds in `pyproject.toml` under `[tool.windsweeper]`.

